****************************************************************************
@Node "Introduction"
@{b}
                                Introduction
@{ub}
Prometer  is  a little program to graphically show the current memory-usage.
It can be used to calculate the difference of free memory between two times.
This can come handy when debugging a program to test for memory-losses.
@EndNode

****************************************************************************
@Node "Requirements"
@{b}
                                Requirements
@{ub}
To run ProMeter you need:
- Kickstart V2.04 or greater.
- reqtools.library (Copyright by Nico François)
@EndNode

****************************************************************************
@Node "InstallWB"
@{b}
                      Installation using the Workbench
@{ub}
Just  copy  ProMeter  and  it's  icon to the directory you want and copy the
Reqtools.library  to  LIBS:.   If  you  are using MagicWB, you can also copy
ProMeter-MWB.icon over ProMeter.info.
@EndNode

****************************************************************************
@Node "Usage"
@{b}
                                   Usage
@{ub}
Doubleclick  the  ProMeter-icon  to start ProMeter.  A window will appear on
your  workbench  screen.   This is the mainwindow and contains the following
items:

@{b}
                                  Gadgets
@{ub}
                           @{"C" link "C-gadget"}@{"                 " link "MemoryIndicators"}
                           @{"F" link "F-gadget"}@{"                 " link "MemoryIndicators"}
                           @{"Remember" link "Remember"}@{"Difference" link "Difference"}
@{b}
                               Pulldown menus
@{ub}
@{bg highlight}Project    Settings@{fg text}
@{"Iconify   " link "Iconify"  }@{"Show kilobytes        " link "Kilobytes"}
@{"About...  " link "About"    }@{"Select Color...       " link "Color"}
@{"Quit      " link "Quit"     }@{"Select Danger Color..." link "DangerColor"}@{bg background}
           @{bg highlight      }@{"Jump to next screen   " link "JumpScreen"}@{bg background}
           @{bg highlight      }@{"Save Settings         " link "SaveSettings"}@{bg background}

Most menu-items have a shortcut key connected to it for faster access.
@EndNode

****************************************************************************
@node "C-gadget"  
 @{b}
                                  C-gadget
@{ub}
When  this  gadget  is  selected, some information about FAST-memory will be
displayed  in  the  menu-bar.  If the Show Kilobytes option is selected, the
values will be displayed in kilobytes otherwise in bytes.

The information looks like:

CHIPMEM - Maximum: xxxx Used: xxxx Free: xxxx
@EndNode
****************************************************************************
@node "F-gadget"
 @{b}
                                  F-gadget
@{ub}
When  this  gadget  is  selected, some information about CHIP-memory will be
displayed  in  the  menu-bar.  If the Show Kilobytes option is selected, the
values will be displayed in kilobytes otherwise in bytes.

The information looks like:

FASTMEM - Maximum: xxxx Used: xxxx Free: xxxx
@EndNode
****************************************************************************
@node "MemoryIndicators"
 @{b}
                             Memory Indicators
@{ub}
There  are  two  indicators in ProMeter's window.  The upper one is for CHIP
memory  and the lower one for FAST memory.  The indicator will be drawn in a
different  color  when  you  are  low  on  memory.  The colours in which the
indicators  are drawn can be selected with the menu-options @{"Select Color" link "Color"} and
@{"Select Danger Color" link "DangerColor"}.

@EndNode
****************************************************************************

@node "Remember"
@{b}
                              Remember-gadget
@{ub}
When  this  gadget is selected the currently free CHIP- and FAST-memory will
be stored. In the titlebar will appear:

Remembering: CHIPMEM   Free: xxxx   FASTMEM   Free: xxxx
@EndNode
****************************************************************************
@node "Difference"
@{b}
                             Difference-gadget
@{ub}
When  this  gadget is selected the currently free CHIP- and FAST-memory will
be  substracted  from the values which were stored with the remember-gadget.
The result will be negative if some memory is allocated in the meanwhile

In the titlebar will appear:

Difference: CHIPMEM   Gained: xxxx   FASTMEM   Gained: xxxx
@EndNode
****************************************************************************
@node "Iconify"
@{b}
                                  Iconify
@{ub}
This function closes the window and puts an icon on the Workbench.  When the
icon is double-clicked the window will be opened again.
@EndNode
****************************************************************************
@node "About"
@{b}
                                   About
@{ub}
This function shows some very important information.
@EndNode

****************************************************************************
@node "Quit"
@{b}
                                    Quit
@{ub}
When you select this, you will immediately leave ProMeter.
@EndNode

****************************************************************************
@node "KiloBytes"
@{b}
                               Show Kilobytes
@{ub}
When  this  option  is  tagged, the strings in the menu-bar will be shown in
Kilobytes instead of bytes.
@EndNode
****************************************************************************
@node "Color"
@{b}
                                   Color
@{ub}
This  function opens a palette-requester.  You should select a color here in
which the memory-indicators should be drawn.
@EndNode
****************************************************************************
@node "DangerColor"
@{b}
                                DangerColor
@{ub}
This  function opens a palette-requester.  You should select a color here in
which the memory-indicators should be drawn if you are low on memory.
@EndNode
****************************************************************************
@node "JumpScreen"
@{b}
                                 JumpScreen
@{ub}
When  this  menuitem  is selected ProMeter will open it's window on the next
screen.
@EndNode
****************************************************************************
@node "SaveSettings"
@{b}
                                SaveSettings
@{ub}
This  option  saves  the current settings to ProMeter's icon.  The following
settings will be saved:

- Window X,Y position.
- Colors used for drawing the memory indicators.
- The show kilobytes option.
@EndNode
